Next one.

00:22:01.000 --> 00:22:02.140 align:middle line:90%
What the heck is this?

00:22:02.140 --> 00:22:03.550 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: Bee hives.

00:22:03.550 --> 00:22:06.335 align:middle line:84%
This is a bee dancing
in a figure eight dance

00:22:06.335 --> 00:22:08.410 align:middle line:84%
and indicating to
other bees where

00:22:08.410 --> 00:22:10.090 align:middle line:90%
it's found honey and nectar.

00:22:10.090 --> 00:22:11.400 align:middle line:90%
There are two kinds of bees.

00:22:11.400 --> 00:22:13.800 align:middle line:84%
Conformist bees and
nonconformist bees.

00:22:13.800 --> 00:22:16.930 align:middle line:84%
The nonconformist bees are
about 5% of the entire hive.

00:22:16.930 --> 00:22:19.375 align:middle line:84%
And they seem to
waste their time.

00:22:19.375 --> 00:22:20.950 align:middle line:90%
You and I are conformist bees.

00:22:20.950 --> 00:22:21.940 align:middle line:84%
We're going out
there and getting

00:22:21.940 --> 00:22:22.875 align:middle line:90%
the pollen and the nectar.

00:22:22.875 --> 00:22:23.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We're
generating things.

00:22:23.990 --> 00:22:25.490 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: These
good-for-nothings are

00:22:25.490 --> 00:22:29.240 align:middle line:84%
out there just roaming around
in these lazy eights for eight

00:22:29.240 --> 00:22:32.630 align:middle line:84%
miles during the day, just
satisfying their own curiosity.

00:22:32.630 --> 00:22:34.570 align:middle line:84%
Why are we even
bothering to feed them?

00:22:34.570 --> 00:22:36.400 align:middle line:84%
Well, it turns out
that when us conformist

00:22:36.400 --> 00:22:39.980 align:middle line:84%
bees run through all the pollen
and nectar in the flower patch

00:22:39.980 --> 00:22:42.940 align:middle line:84%
that we've been mining and have
no clue of where to go next,

00:22:42.940 --> 00:22:45.802 align:middle line:84%
the explorer bees-- the ones who
have been out there seemingly

00:22:45.802 --> 00:22:47.260 align:middle line:84%
just following
their own instincts?

00:22:47.260 --> 00:22:47.780 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They know where to go.

00:22:47.780 --> 00:22:48.488 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: Exactly.

00:22:48.488 --> 00:22:50.740 align:middle line:84%
And they convey it
with this dance.

00:22:50.740 --> 00:22:53.445 align:middle line:84%
And they try to recruit you
and me to go out and check

00:22:53.445 --> 00:22:55.153 align:middle line:84%
their findings and
then come back and act

00:22:55.153 --> 00:22:55.945 align:middle line:90%
as back-up dancers.

00:22:55.945 --> 00:22:56.903 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They're smart.

00:22:56.903 --> 00:22:57.920 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: Yeah, actually.

00:22:57.920 --> 00:22:58.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They may
be smarter than us.

00:22:58.460 --> 00:23:00.340 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: Well, they
form a collective brain.

00:23:00.340 --> 00:23:02.010 align:middle line:90%
They form a search engine.

00:23:02.010 --> 00:23:04.050 align:middle line:84%
They form a collective
intelligence.

00:23:04.050 --> 00:23:07.480 align:middle line:84%
And so do we humans in society
form a collective intelligence.

00:23:07.480 --> 00:23:09.980 align:middle line:84%
You and I are doing the
searcher function right now.

00:23:09.980 --> 00:23:10.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yep.

00:23:10.950 --> 00:23:11.510 align:middle line:90%
Next one.

00:23:11.510 --> 00:23:12.259 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look.

00:23:12.259 --> 00:23:12.960 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: Ah ha.

00:23:12.960 --> 00:23:14.000 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What is that?

00:23:14.000 --> 00:23:16.780 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: You have seen
this tens of thousands

00:23:16.780 --> 00:23:20.810 align:middle line:84%
to hundreds of thousands of
times in your lifetime, George.

